# Destructive operations safety

- Never suggest destructive/irreversible commands by default.
- Do not propose history-rewriting workflows unless explicitly requested.

## Treat as destructive (require explicit request + clear warning)

- `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fdx`, force pushes, rewriting history
- Deleting directories/files as a “fix”
- Bulk search/replace across the repo

## If the user explicitly asks

- Provide a safer alternative first.
- Include a backup/escape hatch step (e.g., branch/tag, copy folder, or stashing).
